article.headline: Dartmouth 78, Columbia 68
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Michael Giovacchini and Mike Lang each had 16 points to help Dartmouth beat Columbia 78-68 on Saturday night and end a seven-game losing streak. Giovacchini started a 12-4 run midway through the second half with a 3-pointer after Columbia (8-11, 1-5 Ivy League) had closed within two. Dartmouth (3-15, 1-5) pulled away to a 54-44 lead with 8:18 to go and the Lions never got closer than five thereafter. John Baumann scored 16 points for the Lions, Ben Nwachukwu added 14 and both Brett Loscalzo and Justin Armstrong had 10. Dartmouth, which matched its season high of 78 points, built an 18-11 lead midway through the first half and led, 27-25, at halftime. Columbia has lost nine of its last 11 games.
